    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The function "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "udf_MonthlyBillingNextPeriod",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value and are often used to encapsulate logic that can be reused across queries. This particular function is designed to calculate the next billing period for a monthly billing cycle based on a given date. It is typically used in financial or subscription-based applications where billing cycles are a key component."
        }
